    "summary": "FINE: Experiential Sequences section is clean, no remaining spoilers",
    "content": "**FINE.**\n\nThe Experiential Sequences section is now clean. The three examples:\n\n- **Essay 3 (line 93):** Describes the method (three cases, mythic to mundane, a recognition the reader must encounter) without revealing the punchline or the specific cases. No spoiler.\n- **Essay 4 (line 95):** Describes the structure (two passes, reversal) including the specific content of both directions. This was debated and voted 8-2 to keep. The reversal is processual — knowing the content does not diminish the experience of tracking it step by step. No spoiler in the damaging sense.\n- **Essay 7 (line 97):** Describes a translation decision. No spoiler.\n\nThe introductory paragraph (line 89) and closing paragraph (line 99) describe the method without revealing any conclusions. The section now does exactly what it should: it tells the reader that the essays are designed as experiential experiments, warns them that sequencing matters, and gives enough concrete detail to be convincing — without abstracting any of the experiences the essays are designed to produce."
